                  </hi>. I live in Fife-court, St. George's-in-the-East. Between one and two o'clock in the morning of the 2nd of Oct., I met the prisoners in Fleet-street—Bowles came in front of me—Wyles went behind—I had not stood a second before Bowles put her hand into my pocket, and took my hand<lb></lb>kerchief out—I turned round, and accused her directly—she said she had not got it—I said, "No, but your companion has"—the policeman came up di<lb></lb>rectly, and picked it up—I saw it pass from Bowles to Wyles.</p>
